WEBVTT

00:01.632 --> 00:04.775
HEY, WANT SOME FLAX
FOR YOUR YOGURT?

00:04.775 --> 00:07.278
IT'S RICH IN OMEGA-3
FATTY ACIDS

00:07.278 --> 00:09.410
AND IT PROMOTES
REGULARITY.

00:09.410 --> 00:11.112
WHO ARE YOU?

00:11.112 --> 00:13.084
[SPOON CLANKS]

00:13.084 --> 00:15.416
HEY, I'M SORRY ANDI
BROKE UP WITH YOU

00:15.416 --> 00:17.288
BECAUSE YOU'RE THE SON
OF THE DEVIL.

00:17.288 --> 00:18.449
AND EVEN THOUGH
YOUR DAD'S EVIL,

00:18.449 --> 00:21.252
I THOUGHT YOU GUYS WERE
A GREAT COUPLE TOGETHER.

00:21.252 --> 00:22.493
NO. NO, DON'T BE SORRY.

00:22.493 --> 00:23.754
I'M NOT READY
TO GIVE UP YET.

00:23.754 --> 00:26.157
IF I KEEP PUSHING,
WORKING SOME ANGLES,

00:26.157 --> 00:27.027
USING MY CHARM,

00:27.027 --> 00:29.160
I KNOW I CAN GET HER BACK.

00:29.160 --> 00:30.030
YOU THINK THAT'S
THE RIGHT IDEA?

00:30.030 --> 00:33.134
I MEAN, MAYBE YOU SHOULD
GIVE IT A LITTLE SPACE
FOR A WHILE.

00:33.134 --> 00:33.664
NO, SPACE IS THE ENEMY.

00:33.664 --> 00:36.307
I'M NOT DONE UNTIL
WE GET BACK TOGETHER.

00:36.307 --> 00:36.807
GOOD FOR YOU.

00:36.807 --> 00:40.441
SOMETIMES YOU'VE GOT TO
LOOK REALITY IN THE FACE
AND SAY NO.

00:40.441 --> 00:41.712
[CHUCKLES] YEAH.

00:41.712 --> 00:44.044
[LIQUID POURING]

00:44.044 --> 00:45.146
MORNING, BUTTHEADS.

00:45.146 --> 00:46.046
OW.
HELLO.

00:46.046 --> 00:47.618
HEY, YOU GUYS SEEN
KRISTEN AROUND?

00:47.618 --> 00:49.580
THINK SHE'S
IN THE SHOWER.

00:49.580 --> 00:52.052
REALLY?

00:54.155 --> 00:56.527
[HUMMING]

00:58.289 --> 00:59.290
OH!

00:59.290 --> 01:00.661
BROUGHT SHOWER COFFEE.

01:00.661 --> 01:01.692
SOCK! WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:01.692 --> 01:04.335
OH, COME ON,
I'VE SEEN YOUR CASH
AND PRIZES BEFORE.

01:04.335 --> 01:06.337
GET OUT!
MY FATHER WILL CATCH US.

01:06.337 --> 01:09.069
WHAT? RELAX. MY MOM
AND YOUR DAD MOVED OUT.

01:09.069 --> 01:09.800
WE'RE GOOD.

01:09.800 --> 01:11.071
THEY COULD VISIT ANYTIME.

01:11.071 --> 01:13.104
THIS IS NOT ACCEPTABLE.

01:13.104 --> 01:14.375
WHAT? [SCOFFS]

01:14.375 --> 01:15.176
COME ON.

01:15.176 --> 01:16.076
WHAT ARE YOU
SO WORRIED ABOUT?

01:16.076 --> 01:19.110
MY FATHER CANNOT
KNOW I DATE
MY STEPBROTHER.

01:19.110 --> 01:21.512
ALL RIGHT, SURE, LOOK,
HE'LL BE SHOCKED
AT FIRST, YEAH,

01:21.512 --> 01:25.316
BUT SO IS THE FATHER
OF EVERY GIRL I'VE
EVER DATED, ALL RIGHT?

01:25.316 --> 01:26.817
BUT EVENTUALLY,
I PROMISE YOU,

01:26.817 --> 01:29.660
HE WILL SETTLE INTO
A NICE, GRUDGING ACCEPTANCE.

01:29.660 --> 01:30.861
NO, YOU DON'T KNOW
MY FATHER.

01:30.861 --> 01:33.664
HE DOES NOT CHANGE
HIS MIND. EVER.

01:33.664 --> 01:34.395
[SPOON CLANKING]

01:34.395 --> 01:37.168
GO ON.
DON'T LET ME INTERRUPT.

01:37.168 --> 01:38.199
[GASPS]

01:38.199 --> 01:40.201
OH, COME--OH, COME ON.

01:40.201 --> 01:42.373
[SIGHS]
CAN YOU BELIEVE THIS?

01:42.373 --> 01:45.506
[GRUNTS] SHE DOESN'T THINK
THAT I CAN CHARM HER FATHER.

01:45.506 --> 01:46.377
ME.

01:46.377 --> 01:47.208
UNBELIEVABLE.

01:47.208 --> 01:48.709
I KNOW, IT'S NUTS.

01:48.709 --> 01:49.810
COULD YOU PUT SOME
CLOTHES ON, PLEASE?

01:49.810 --> 01:52.143
I'M TOO UPSET
FOR CLOTHES, MAN.

01:52.143 --> 01:54.185
OOH, IS THAT FLAX?

01:54.185 --> 01:54.445
UGH.

01:54.445 --> 01:57.188
THIS STUFF'S
REALLY GOOD FOR YOU.

02:08.529 --> 02:11.202
AW, MAN, SO HOT.

02:11.202 --> 02:13.164
UGH. CORPORATE'S
MAKING ME FILL OUT

02:13.164 --> 02:14.865
ALL THESE STUPID
RESPONSIBILITY
MATRIX FORMS.

02:14.865 --> 02:16.307
I SWEAR TO GOD, IF I
DON'T TAKE A BREAK,

02:16.307 --> 02:18.169
I'M GONNA KILL
SOMEONE.

02:18.169 --> 02:21.172
MMM. YOU GUYS
WANT TO SEE
A MOVIE TONIGHT?

02:21.172 --> 02:22.473
BLOODIER THE BETTER.

02:22.473 --> 02:26.146
[CLEARS THROAT]
I CHOOSE SAM.

02:26.146 --> 02:27.518
HMM? WHAT?

02:27.518 --> 02:30.451
YOU GUYS BROKE UP,
I HAD TO CHOOSE A SIDE.

02:30.451 --> 02:31.382
I CHOSE SAM.

02:31.382 --> 02:33.824
WAIT, WHY DO YOU
HAVE TO CHOOSE
ANY SIDE?

02:33.824 --> 02:35.656
[CHUCKLES] OK.

02:35.656 --> 02:37.157
I KNOW WHAT YOU'RE
TRYING TO DO HERE, ANDI.

02:37.157 --> 02:39.530
THIS IS AN UGLY
AND AWKWARD SITUATION.

02:39.530 --> 02:41.632
I MADE A CHOICE,
IT'S SAM, LIVE WITH IT.

02:41.632 --> 02:44.495
NOBODY'S SAYING THAT WE
DON'T WANT TO BE FRIENDS
IN THE FUTURE, OK?

02:44.495 --> 02:46.837
WE JUST THINK THAT
IN THE TIME BEING

02:46.837 --> 02:48.499
MAYBE WE SHOULD
TAKE A BREAK.

02:48.499 --> 02:49.900
A FRIENDSHIP BREAK.

02:49.900 --> 02:52.373
WHILE SAM HEALS.

02:52.373 --> 02:53.674
HMM.

02:53.674 --> 02:54.745
THAT'S TOO BAD,

02:54.745 --> 02:56.277
'CAUSE I HAD
A PRETTY COOL
ASSIGNMENT

02:56.277 --> 02:58.349
I WAS GONNA THROW TO
A COUPLE OF FRIENDS.

02:58.349 --> 02:59.210
A COOL ASSIGNMENT?

02:59.210 --> 03:01.882
MM-HMM. OH, WE
JUST GOT IN A NEW
SHIPMENT OF HAMMOCKS,

03:01.882 --> 03:03.183
REALLY NICE ONES,

03:03.183 --> 03:05.886
AND I NEED PEOPLE TO
STRETCH TEST THEM.

03:05.886 --> 03:06.657
STRETCH TEST?

03:06.657 --> 03:08.719
YEAH, YOU KNOW,
SLEEP IN THEM FOR
A FEW HOURS,

03:08.719 --> 03:09.560
SEE HOW
THEY HOLD UP.

03:09.560 --> 03:11.191
I CHOOSE YOU!
I'M ON YOUR SIDE.

03:11.191 --> 03:11.662
BREAK'S OVER.

03:11.662 --> 03:14.865
OK, WHEN DO WE START?
ARE THEY HERE?

03:14.865 --> 03:17.228
THOUGHT SO.

03:22.773 --> 03:24.905
UH, TRY NOT TO
CHEW ON IT, OK?

03:24.905 --> 03:28.879
REMEMBER
WHAT HAPPENED TO
YOUR SQUEAKY TOY?

03:32.383 --> 03:35.686
NONE OF MY OTHER
GIRLFRIENDS EVER PLAYED
FETCH WITH ME.

03:35.686 --> 03:38.549
I LIKE TO BE SPECIAL.

03:39.690 --> 03:41.552
BABY.

03:41.552 --> 03:45.996
HEY, GUESS WHAT
SATURDAY IS?

03:45.996 --> 03:49.229
OUR 2-MONTH ANNIVERSARY.

03:49.229 --> 03:50.931
YOU'RE RIGHT.

03:50.931 --> 03:54.004
WOW. 2 MONTHS AGO
I KIDNAPPED YOU

03:54.004 --> 03:55.936
AND FORCED YOU
TO BE MY BOYFRIEND.

03:55.936 --> 03:57.808
OH, THE DETAILS
DON'T MATTER.

03:57.808 --> 04:01.642
WHAT MATTERS IS I WANT
TO DO SOMETHING SPECIAL
FOR OUR OCCASION.

04:01.642 --> 04:03.444
ANYTHING YOU WANT
TO DO, OK?

04:03.444 --> 04:07.518
UNLESS IT INVOLVES
SACRIFICING AN ANIMAL.

04:07.518 --> 04:08.419
OH.

04:08.419 --> 04:09.450
BUT ANYTHING ELSE,
I'M IN.

04:09.450 --> 04:11.982
YOU KNOW WHAT,
THERE IS SOMETHING
THAT I WANT TO DO.

04:11.982 --> 04:14.325
IT'S SOMETHING THAT'S
REALLY IMPORTANT TO ME,

04:14.325 --> 04:18.959
AND I THINK IT'LL TAKE
OUR RELATIONSHIP
TO THE NEXT LEVEL.

04:18.959 --> 04:20.661
REVERSE COWGIRL.

04:20.661 --> 04:21.792
NO. [LAUGHS]

04:21.792 --> 04:24.565
NO, SILLY, I WANT TO
TAKE YOU FLYING.

04:24.565 --> 04:26.897
OH, RIGHT, YEAH,
FLYING.

04:26.897 --> 04:29.340
IT'S SUCH AN AMAZING
EXPERIENCE, BEN.

04:29.340 --> 04:31.902
AT NIGHT, I GO UP
TO THE MOUNTAINS,

04:31.902 --> 04:33.804
AND I SWERVE
THROUGH THE CLOUDS,

04:33.804 --> 04:36.046
AND I BUZZ ALONG
THE TREETOPS.

04:36.046 --> 04:37.478
IT'S SO MOVING, BABY.

04:37.478 --> 04:39.980
AND I REALLY WANT TO
SHARE IT WITH YOU.

04:39.980 --> 04:43.414
IT SOUNDS AWESOME.

04:43.414 --> 04:44.485
REALLY?

04:44.485 --> 04:46.286
WELL, LET'S GO
RIGHT NOW.

04:46.286 --> 04:48.519
NO, LET'S NOT.

04:48.519 --> 04:49.420
WHY?

04:49.420 --> 04:52.923
I THINK WE SHOULD SAVE
SOMETHING SO SPECIAL

04:52.923 --> 04:55.826
FOR OUR SPECIAL DAY,
THAT'S ALL.

04:55.826 --> 04:57.498
YOU'RE RIGHT.

04:57.498 --> 04:57.998
YOU'RE RIGHT.

04:57.998 --> 05:00.030
OK, WE'LL SAVE IT
FOR SATURDAY.

05:00.030 --> 05:02.533
OH, THIS IS GONNA BE
SO GREAT.

05:02.533 --> 05:07.978
YEAH, GREAT.

05:07.978 --> 05:09.440
I JUST DON'T UNDERSTAND.

05:09.440 --> 05:12.443
I MEAN, THIS IS LIKE
EVERY RELATIONSHIP
I'VE EVER BEEN IN.

05:12.443 --> 05:14.415
THERE'S ALWAYS
A FATAL FLAW.

05:14.415 --> 05:15.886
WHAT'S THE FATAL FLAW
THIS TIME?

05:15.886 --> 05:17.848
NINA WANTS TO
TAKE ME FLYING,

05:17.848 --> 05:18.819
BUT I CAN'T.

05:18.819 --> 05:20.050
I DON'T WANT TO DIE.

05:20.050 --> 05:22.923
WELL, HAVE YOU TRIED
TELLING HER HOW
YOU REALLY FEEL?

05:22.923 --> 05:24.955
OK, SHH. TUT-TUT.

05:24.955 --> 05:26.627
TALKING ABOUT FEELINGS, SAM?
COME ON.

05:26.627 --> 05:29.360
WE'RE DISCUSSING BEN'S
FATAL FLAW, ALL RIGHT,

05:29.360 --> 05:29.930
NOT YOURS.

05:29.930 --> 05:31.632
BENJAMIN, LOOK AT ME.
COME HERE.

05:31.632 --> 05:32.403
LOOK AT ME.

05:32.403 --> 05:33.534
I WANT YOU
TO FORGET ALL ABOUT

05:33.534 --> 05:34.865
THIS FATAL FLAW POPPYCOCK.

05:34.865 --> 05:35.966
IT IS NONSENSE,
ALL RIGHT?

05:35.966 --> 05:37.908
YOU ARE GOING TO FLY.

05:37.908 --> 05:40.110
YOU THINK SO?
I KNOW SO, BUDDY.

05:40.110 --> 05:42.342
BRING IT IN. HUG.

05:42.342 --> 05:44.575
GO GET HER!

05:44.875 --> 05:46.717
[SIGHS]
IT'S SO SAD.

05:46.717 --> 05:49.520
SHE'S TOTALLY DUMPING HIM.

05:50.921 --> 05:52.883
GREAT.
WHAT THE HELL IS
MORGAN DOING BACK?

05:52.883 --> 05:55.125
OH, HE'S HERE?
I MISS THAT GUY.

05:55.125 --> 05:56.857
LITTLE BIT.

05:58.889 --> 06:00.931
AFTERNOON, FELLAS.

06:00.931 --> 06:02.132
WHAT'S SHAKING,
MORGAN?

06:02.132 --> 06:04.395
LET ME TELL YOU
WHERE I WAS 12 HOURS AGO.

06:04.395 --> 06:05.466
THE FRENCH RIVIERA,

06:05.466 --> 06:09.470
SURROUNDED BY TOPLESS
SUPER MODELS AND CHAMPAGNE.

06:09.470 --> 06:12.603
AND NOW I'M HERE,
AT THE WORK BENCH,

06:12.603 --> 06:13.974
SURROUNDED BY
TOILET PLUNGERS.

06:13.974 --> 06:15.406
WELL, YOU DIDN'T
HAVE TO COME BACK.

06:15.406 --> 06:18.008
NOT TRUE, SAMMY BOY.
DAD ORDERED ME TO.

06:18.008 --> 06:21.652
WANTED ME TO DO MORE
OF THAT TRAINING STUFF
WITH YOU.

06:21.652 --> 06:22.883
JUST BELIEVE
IN YOURSELF.

06:22.883 --> 06:25.516
THERE,
TRAINING COMPLETE.

06:25.956 --> 06:28.018
SAM, YOU KNOW AND I KNOW

06:28.018 --> 06:29.920
THAT I'M REALLY BAD
AT THIS JOB,

06:29.920 --> 06:31.962
BUT YOU WERE BORN FOR IT.

06:31.962 --> 06:32.893
YOU'RE GREAT AT THIS.

06:32.893 --> 06:34.725
AND I'M ABOVE IT.
NO OFFENSE.

06:34.725 --> 06:36.867
SO, I HAVE
A PROPOSITION FOR YOU.

06:36.867 --> 06:38.529
YOU CATCH A SOUL FOR ME,

06:38.529 --> 06:41.171
AND I'LL GIVE YOU $10,000.

06:41.171 --> 06:44.635
MORGAN, NO. I DO NOT
WORK FOR YOU.

06:44.635 --> 06:47.678
FAIR ENOUGH.

06:47.678 --> 06:48.839
20,000.

06:48.839 --> 06:49.139
MORGAN, NO.

06:49.139 --> 06:52.412
NO, HO HO HO.
HOLD ON. HOLD ON ONE SEC.

06:52.412 --> 06:53.684
WE'VE GOT TO CATCH
THE GUY ANYWAY.

06:53.684 --> 06:55.986
WHY NOT MAKE A
LITTLE EXTRA CHEESE
IN THE MEANTIME?

06:55.986 --> 06:57.087
WE DON'T NEED
HIS MONEY.

06:57.087 --> 07:00.050
I NEED HIS MONEY.
I WANT HIS MONEY, SAM.

07:00.050 --> 07:00.651
FOR WHAT?

07:00.651 --> 07:02.793
FOR A NEW HOT WATER
HEATER AND JET SKIS.

07:02.793 --> 07:03.654
IT DOESN'T MATTER
WHAT FOR.

07:03.654 --> 07:04.855
LISTEN, DON'T WE DESERVE
A LITTLE SOMETHING

07:04.855 --> 07:08.599
TO SHOW FOR ALL
THE CRAP WE PUT UP WITH
AROUND HERE, JUST ONCE?

07:08.599 --> 07:10.000
ALL RIGHT.

07:10.000 --> 07:11.832
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT.

07:11.832 --> 07:12.733
WHOO-HOO.

07:12.733 --> 07:14.565
SO, YOU CATCH ME
THE SOUL,

07:14.565 --> 07:15.706
I'LL TAKE CREDIT,

07:15.706 --> 07:16.907
DAD'S OFF OF MY BACK,

07:16.907 --> 07:18.068
AND I'M OUT OF YOUR HAIR.

07:18.068 --> 07:20.841
AND YOU'RE ALL
THE RICHER FOR IT.

07:20.841 --> 07:21.872
OHH.

07:21.872 --> 07:23.213
HEY, MAN.

07:26.977 --> 07:29.620
[PAPER RUSTLING]

07:46.637 --> 07:49.039
[MEN SHOUTING]

07:51.001 --> 07:53.644
[GROANING]

07:54.675 --> 07:57.107
CAN YOU SMELL IT, SAMMY?

07:57.107 --> 07:59.109
SWEAT AND CIGARETTES?

07:59.109 --> 08:01.952
DESPERATION.

08:01.952 --> 08:04.755
INTOXICATING.

08:05.085 --> 08:09.159
HEY, MY BOY MORGAN
SHOW HIS FACE YET?

08:09.159 --> 08:12.893
UH, YEAH. YEAH.
EVERYTHING'S FINE.

08:12.893 --> 08:14.795
HE'S GOING TO HELP
WITH THE NEXT SOUL.

08:14.795 --> 08:16.767
AH, THAT'S WHAT
I WANTED TO HEAR.

08:16.767 --> 08:17.998
I KNEW WE JUST HAD
TO LIGHT A FIRE

08:17.998 --> 08:19.930
TO THAT KID'S
REAR END.

08:19.930 --> 08:20.871
[LAUGHS]

08:20.871 --> 08:23.534
SPEAKING OF NEXT SOUL.

08:23.534 --> 08:24.935
OH, WAIT.

08:24.935 --> 08:28.979
WAIT. UH, ACTUALLY
NEVER MIND.

08:28.979 --> 08:31.612
I DON'T FEEL PROUD
ABOUT THIS ONE, SAM.

08:31.612 --> 08:33.043
I MEAN,
ONE COULD SAY THAT
I'M EVEN FEELING

08:33.043 --> 08:35.285
A LITTLE GUILTY
ABOUT IT, YOU KNOW.

08:35.285 --> 08:36.587
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

08:36.587 --> 08:39.990
WELL, HE WAS KILLED
WHILE COVETING.

08:39.990 --> 08:41.051
SO?

08:41.051 --> 08:42.553
SO, IT'S
THE COMMANDMENT.

08:42.553 --> 08:46.126
THOU SHALT NOT COVET
THY NEIGHBOR'S WIFE.

08:46.126 --> 08:48.829
THIS POOR SCHMUCK
WAS MENTALLY UNDRESSING
SOME BROAD,

08:48.829 --> 08:50.731
THEN THE NEXT
INSTANT--BAM.

08:50.731 --> 08:51.962
HIT BY A TRUCK.

08:51.962 --> 08:53.033
HE WAS JUST LOOKING AT HER?

08:53.033 --> 08:54.164
DIDN'T HAVE SEX WITH HER?

08:54.164 --> 08:55.305
NO.
THAT IS STUPID.

08:55.305 --> 08:56.937
YEAH, TELL ME ABOUT IT.

08:56.937 --> 08:58.669
YOU KNOW,
IN THE OLD DAYS

08:58.669 --> 09:00.941
I USED TO GET THE SOULS
THAT ATE SHRIMP.

09:00.941 --> 09:04.044
CAN YOU IMAGINE HOW
UNSATISFYING THAT WAS?

09:04.044 --> 09:04.815
[STAMMERS]

09:04.815 --> 09:07.948
WAIT, SO YOU CAN
GO TO HELL FOR JUST
THINKING OF SOMETHING?

09:07.948 --> 09:09.049
YEAH. DON'T BLAME ME.

09:09.049 --> 09:11.622
I DIDN'T MAKE THE RULES.

09:11.622 --> 09:13.053
[CHUCKLES]

09:13.053 --> 09:16.226
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE RIGHT.

09:16.226 --> 09:18.689
WHY SHOULD I FEEL GUILTY
ABOUT THIS?

09:18.689 --> 09:20.961
[GROANS]
THIS ONE'S
ON THE BIG GUY.

09:20.961 --> 09:22.963
[CHUCKLES] HEY.

09:22.963 --> 09:25.996
NOW, GET ME
MY SOUL BACK.

09:29.039 --> 09:31.672
GUY'S NAMED
BILLY BOYLAND.

09:31.672 --> 09:32.703
DIED BACK IN
THE EARLY NINETIES.

09:32.703 --> 09:36.246
THIS WAS ONE OF HIS
FAVORITE HANGOUTS BACK THEN.

09:38.108 --> 09:39.279
EXCUSE ME.
EXCUSE ME.

09:39.279 --> 09:40.050
HI, CAN I GET...

09:40.050 --> 09:41.882
STILL IS.
LOOK OVER THERE.

09:41.882 --> 09:43.083
A LITTLE BIT
OF WHIPPED CREAM

09:43.083 --> 09:45.085
AND 2 CHERRIES.

09:47.718 --> 09:49.990
HEH. HI.

09:49.990 --> 09:51.321
HEY, BILLY.

09:51.321 --> 09:53.664
DO I KNOW YOU GUYS?

09:53.664 --> 09:54.264
MM-MMM.

09:54.264 --> 09:56.026
IS THAT A DODGEBALL?

09:56.026 --> 09:56.596
GOOD GUESS.

09:56.596 --> 09:58.729
WELL, YEAH, I'VE HAD
A LOT OF THOSE

09:58.729 --> 09:59.970
THROWN AT ME
OVER THE YEARS.

09:59.970 --> 10:03.033
IT'S ALSO A VESSEL
TO SEND YOU BACK TO HELL.

10:03.033 --> 10:04.635
[SIGHS]

10:04.635 --> 10:06.106
[GROANS]

10:06.106 --> 10:07.838
COME ON, I DON'T WANT
TO CAUSE ANY TROUBLE,

10:07.838 --> 10:10.310
BUT I MEAN, YOU GUYS
KNOW WHY I WENT
TO HELL, DON'T YOU?

10:10.310 --> 10:13.043
COVETING? ISN'T THAT
A LITTLE UNFAIR?

10:13.043 --> 10:14.985
HEARD EVERY EXCUSE
IN THE BOOK,
BILLY BOY.

10:14.985 --> 10:16.086
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

10:16.086 --> 10:17.287
DO IT NOW.
NOBODY'S LOOKING.

10:17.287 --> 10:18.118
NO, NO.
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

10:18.118 --> 10:20.150
PLEASE, JUST LET ME EAT
MY DESSERT FIRST.

10:20.150 --> 10:24.054
ETERNITY IS SUCH
A LONG TIME FOR NO PIE.

10:24.054 --> 10:26.026
OK, FINE, FINE.
HURRY UP.

10:26.026 --> 10:29.059
THANK YOU.
THANK YOU.

10:29.059 --> 10:31.331
IT'S DELICIOUS.

10:31.331 --> 10:32.262
YOU WANT SOME?

10:32.262 --> 10:34.134
SURE, I WOULDN'T MIND.

10:34.134 --> 10:34.935
[FORK CLATTERS]

10:34.935 --> 10:38.008
OH. DON'T WORRY.
SORRY. I GOT IT.

10:38.008 --> 10:40.110
HERE, HAVE SOME.

10:42.973 --> 10:44.014
OH,
THAT'S NOT BAD.

10:44.014 --> 10:45.976
VESSEL HIM NOW,
THE PIE'S OURS.

10:45.976 --> 10:48.148
UH, WHERE'D HE GO?

10:48.148 --> 10:50.981
WHAT?
HUH?

10:50.981 --> 10:53.223
THERE HE IS!
THERE HE IS!

10:53.854 --> 10:56.056
SON OF A BUN!

