22:12.932 --> 22:14.333
NO, OF LOVING MYSELF

22:14.333 --> 22:16.766
AND LETTING MYSELF
BY LOVED.

22:16.766 --> 22:17.507
OH.

22:17.507 --> 22:18.868
AND THAT'S
GOOD NEWS?

22:18.868 --> 22:21.541
THAT'S GREAT NEWS
BECAUSE I FIGURED IT OUT--

22:21.541 --> 22:22.512
HOW TO LOVE MYSELF.

22:22.512 --> 22:25.675
I JUST HAVE TO REMEMBER
HOW WONDERFUL I AM.

22:25.675 --> 22:28.578
AND THAT'S WHERE THIS
COMES IN.

22:29.348 --> 22:30.380
MY VISION BOARD.

22:30.380 --> 22:34.554
IT CONSTANTLY REMINDS ME
OF MY BEST QUALITIES.

22:34.554 --> 22:36.386
"FRIENDLY." THAT'S ME.

22:36.386 --> 22:38.728
I LOVE THAT ABOUT MYSELF.
I'M VERY FRIENDLY.

22:38.728 --> 22:40.390
THE BROOKLYN BRIDGE.

22:40.390 --> 22:41.761
I'M JUST LIKE THAT BRIDGE.

22:41.761 --> 22:43.032
I BRING PEOPLE TOGETHER.

22:43.032 --> 22:45.595
I DO NOT COLLAPSE
UNDER PRESSURE.

22:45.595 --> 22:50.500
THESE GUYS, JUST LIKE ME
WITH SOCK AND SAM.

22:50.500 --> 22:54.404
BOYS, FRIENDSHIP,
BROMANCE.

22:54.404 --> 22:57.076
IS ANY OF THIS MAKING SENSE?

22:57.076 --> 22:58.648
I THINK SO.

22:58.648 --> 23:02.412
SO, DO YOU WANT TO
GO FLYING TOMORROW
OR NOT?

23:02.412 --> 23:04.514
I DO.
I ABSOLUTELY DO.

23:04.514 --> 23:07.587
TOMORROW NIGHT
FOR OUR SPECIAL ANNIVERSARY,

23:07.587 --> 23:09.889
YOU AND ME, WE'RE
FLYING TO THE MOON.

23:09.889 --> 23:10.690
[LAUGHS]

23:10.690 --> 23:16.626
BABY, YOU WOULD
SUFFOCATE AND FREEZE
BEFORE WE GOT THERE.

23:17.867 --> 23:20.069
BUT OK, TOMORROW.

23:20.069 --> 23:21.170
[CLEARS THROAT]

23:21.170 --> 23:22.432
HEY,
WHAT'S THAT ONE?

23:22.432 --> 23:26.506
OH, NOTHING,
I JUST LIKE BUNNIES.

23:27.136 --> 23:28.578
Sock: OH, GOD.

23:28.578 --> 23:29.609
AHH.

23:29.609 --> 23:32.011
OH, POPPA WEEWEE,
THAT'S COLD.

23:32.011 --> 23:33.513
OHH!

23:33.513 --> 23:34.844
[LAUGHS]

23:34.844 --> 23:36.746
WHERE ARE YOUR WADERS?

23:36.746 --> 23:39.489
HUH? WADERS?
I DON'T NEED THEM.

23:39.489 --> 23:40.119
I LIKE TO FEEL
THE WATER.

23:40.119 --> 23:42.522
IT HELPS ME LOCATE
THE FISH.
KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

23:42.522 --> 23:43.453
[CASTS FISHING ROD]

23:43.453 --> 23:44.694
HERE WE GO.

23:44.694 --> 23:47.056
ALL RIGHT.

23:47.927 --> 23:48.928
OHH.

23:48.928 --> 23:50.730
OK.

23:51.160 --> 23:53.533
I GOT IT.

23:53.533 --> 23:55.535
YOU ARE
A TERRIBLE FISHERMAN.

23:55.535 --> 23:58.167
YEAH. YOU KNOW,
I JUST THOUGHT MAYBE
IT'D BE A GOOD IDEA

23:58.167 --> 24:00.740
FOR YOU AND I
TO COME OUT HERE
AND BOND A LITTLE.

24:00.740 --> 24:02.441
YOU KNOW, SPEND SOME
QUALITY TIME TOGETHER.

24:02.441 --> 24:04.213
I MEAN, LOOK AT THIS.
LOOK WHAT WE'RE HAVING.

24:04.213 --> 24:06.015
GOOD TIMES. G.T.s.

24:06.015 --> 24:07.547
YES, GOOD TIMES.

24:07.547 --> 24:08.518
UH-HUH.

24:08.518 --> 24:14.584
LISTEN, UH, I FEEL LIKE
I COULD, UH, I COULD
ASK YOU ANYTHING, DAD.

24:14.584 --> 24:15.625
SO HERE'S ONE FOR YOU,

24:15.625 --> 24:18.127
AND, UH, THIS IS
PURELY HYPOTHETICAL,
BY THE WAY.

24:18.127 --> 24:24.564
WHAT IF, UH, YOU KNOW,
I WANTED TO ASK YOUR
DAUGHTER OUT ON A DATE?

24:24.564 --> 24:26.195
[LAUGHS]

24:26.195 --> 24:27.897
[LAUGHS]

24:28.237 --> 24:29.839
THAT IS OUTRAGEOUS
TO CONSIDER.

24:29.839 --> 24:31.971
YEAH. YEAH, I KNOW,
BUT I'M SERIOUS,
THOUGH.

24:31.971 --> 24:35.505
YOU KNOW, I KNOW
THE WHOLE STEPSISTER,
STEPBROTHER THING

24:35.505 --> 24:36.105
IS A LITTLE WEIRD.

24:36.105 --> 24:38.177
THAT'S OF NO IMPORTANCE.

24:38.177 --> 24:39.809
LOOK, SOCK,

24:39.809 --> 24:42.652
YOU'RE CERTAINLY
A NICE BOY.

24:42.652 --> 24:43.252
THANK YOU.

24:43.252 --> 24:46.055
AND, UH, A FUNNY
KIND OF CLOWN.

24:46.055 --> 24:48.257
HA. YOU COULD JUST
SAY CHARMING.

24:48.257 --> 24:50.259
KRISTEN WOULD NOT DATE YOU.

24:50.259 --> 24:52.792
YOU AREN'T GOOD ENOUGH
FOR HER.

24:52.792 --> 24:55.725
EXCUSE ME.
NOT GOOD ENOUGH?

24:55.725 --> 24:58.768
YOU HAVE SILLY CLOWN HAIR

24:58.768 --> 25:01.771
AND BIG HONKING
CLOWN NOSE.

25:01.771 --> 25:03.072
HONK HONK.

25:03.072 --> 25:05.234
[MOCKING LAUGHTER]

25:05.234 --> 25:06.105
OH, IS THAT FUNNY?

25:06.105 --> 25:07.276
REALLY FUNNY.
I'M A BIG LAUGH
TO YOU, HUH?

25:07.276 --> 25:09.508
WELL, CHECK THIS OUT.
YOUR DAUGHTER
WASN'T LAUGHING

25:09.508 --> 25:12.181
WHEN SHE GAVE HERSELF
TO ME.

25:13.112 --> 25:14.584
SO...

25:14.584 --> 25:17.717
YOU...SOILED MY DAUGHTER?

25:17.717 --> 25:19.248
SOILED? NO.
NO, NO, NO.

25:19.248 --> 25:20.550
NO, NOT SOILED.
NO, NO.

25:20.550 --> 25:22.622
I MADE
THE SWEETEST LOVE
TO YOUR DAUGHTER.

25:22.622 --> 25:24.223
YOU KNOW, I CHERISHED
HER VIRGINITY.

25:24.223 --> 25:26.195
I CHERISHED
EVERY MOMENT OF IT.

25:26.195 --> 25:27.857
[GRUNTS]

25:27.857 --> 25:28.658
NO, NO! OW!

25:28.658 --> 25:30.299
WHAT THE HELL
WAS THAT FOR?

25:30.299 --> 25:31.801
OW! OW!
ALL RIGHT!

25:31.801 --> 25:33.262
WHAT DO YOU--
WHAT DO YOU
WANT ME--

25:33.262 --> 25:35.234
[GRUNTING]
[GROANING]

25:38.037 --> 25:40.239
[GASPING]

25:41.971 --> 25:44.313
[DOG BARKING]

25:48.117 --> 25:50.179
HEY, SAM.
HOW ARE YOU?

25:50.179 --> 25:51.681
UH, I'M DOING ALL RIGHT.

25:51.681 --> 25:53.883
I JUST WANTED
TO CHECK ON YOU.

25:53.883 --> 25:56.686
OH, IT'S ALL GOOD
IN HERE.

25:56.686 --> 25:57.556
[RUSTLING]

25:57.556 --> 25:58.858
YOU, UH, STILL
A GRAPE GUY?

25:58.858 --> 26:00.790
UH, NO THANKS.

26:00.790 --> 26:03.833
DO YOU HAVE
A SECOND TO TALK?

26:03.833 --> 26:06.235
YEAH, SURE.

26:06.235 --> 26:09.639
AND NOW I'M SUPPOSED
TO SEND THIS GUY
BILLY BACK TO HELL,

26:09.639 --> 26:10.269
EVEN THOUGH
HE'S NOT EVIL

26:10.269 --> 26:13.072
AND EVEN THOUGH
HE FOUND THE LOVE
OF HIS LIFE.

26:13.072 --> 26:14.744
SAM, I ACTUALLY
ENVY THE GUY.

26:14.744 --> 26:16.976
I'D RATHER BE A SOUL
RUNNING FREE FOR ONE DAY

26:16.976 --> 26:19.208
THAN TO BE STUCK
IN THIS DECAYING BODY
FOREVER.

26:19.208 --> 26:23.112
I MEAN, HE'S OUT THERE
GETTING FRIENDLY
WITH THE LADIES.

26:23.112 --> 26:26.155
I CAN'T EVEN GET CLOSE
TO YOUR MOM OR...

26:26.155 --> 26:28.117
ANY OTHER WOMAN
FOR THAT MATTER.

26:28.117 --> 26:29.759
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT,

26:29.759 --> 26:31.891
BECAUSE YOU'RE
A DECAYING BODY.

26:31.891 --> 26:34.363
THANKS, SAM.
RUB IT IN.

26:34.363 --> 26:36.125
NO. NO, I'M SAYING,

26:36.125 --> 26:37.266
I THINK
I HAVE AN IDEA

26:37.266 --> 26:40.129
FOR HOW TO KEEP
BILLY OUT OF HELL.

26:40.730 --> 26:42.001
Ben: I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT THIS.

26:42.001 --> 26:42.802
Sam: NO, THIS IS
GONNA WORK.

26:42.802 --> 26:44.133
IT HAS TO,
'CAUSE I DON'T HAVE
ANY OTHER IDEAS.

26:44.133 --> 26:46.676
I DON'T KNOW.
I MEAN, DIGGING UP
A GRAVE SEEMS WRONG.

26:46.676 --> 26:49.238
I MEAN, DISTURBING
THE DEAD IS SOME
BAD MOJO.

26:49.238 --> 26:50.880
IN THIS CASE,
THE DEAD IS ACROSS TOWN

26:50.880 --> 26:52.341
SLEEPING AT HIS
NEW GIRLFRIEND'S HOUSE.

26:52.341 --> 26:54.083
WE'RE JUST DISTURBING
HIS OLD CORPSE.

26:54.083 --> 26:55.214
SO YOU THINK
THAT DODGEBALL'S

26:55.214 --> 26:56.145
GONNA WORK ON
HIS DEAD BODY?

26:56.145 --> 26:57.747
MAYBE HELL WILL THINK
IT'S A MIX-UP.

26:57.747 --> 26:59.218
IF NOT, WE GOT TO SEND
BILLY BACK.

26:59.218 --> 27:01.220
EH, EITHER WAY
WE GET TO ENJOY
THE NIGHT AIR

27:01.220 --> 27:03.022
AND DESECRATE
A CEMETERY.

27:03.022 --> 27:04.223
Ben: FOUND IT.
OOH.

27:04.223 --> 27:09.028
"BILLY BOYLAND.
BORN 1971. DIED 1993."

27:09.028 --> 27:11.330
DUG UP 2009.

27:11.330 --> 27:13.302
UGH.

27:21.210 --> 27:22.942
SO HOW'D IT GO
WITH YOU AND
KRISTEN'S DAD?

27:22.942 --> 27:25.214
OH, WELL,
HE CALLED ME A CLOWN,

27:25.214 --> 27:27.046
SAID I WASN'T GOOD ENOUGH
TO DATE KRISTEN,

27:27.046 --> 27:28.417
AND ATTACKED ME
WITH A FISHING ROD.

27:28.417 --> 27:31.420
HAD TO ESCAPE BY
SWIMMING ACROSS THE LAKE.

27:31.420 --> 27:32.351
THAT'S TERRIBLE, SOCK.

27:32.351 --> 27:36.085
WELL, HONESTLY,
COMPARED TO SOME OTHER TIMES
WHEN I'VE MET THE PARENTS,

27:36.085 --> 27:37.656
IT DIDN'T GO
THAT BADLY, BENJI.

27:37.656 --> 27:39.428
YOU KNOW, HE DIDN'T
PULL A GUN ON ME,

27:39.428 --> 27:41.731
DIDN'T TRY TO RIP OFF
MY GENITALS.

27:41.731 --> 27:44.293
SOUNDS LIKE HE'S GOT
A SOFT SPOT FOR YOU.

27:44.293 --> 27:46.365
FINISHED.
OH, YEAH?

27:46.365 --> 27:47.837
[CASKET CREAKS]

27:47.837 --> 27:49.668
WHOA!
UGH!

27:49.668 --> 27:51.000
IS THAT BILLY?

27:51.000 --> 27:52.441
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
THAT IS.

27:52.441 --> 27:54.443
HE WAS HIT
BY A TRUCK.

27:54.443 --> 27:56.245
YEAH.

27:56.776 --> 27:58.908
ALL RIGHT.
YEP.

27:59.308 --> 28:01.680
WHOA!
AHH.

28:01.680 --> 28:04.253
YOU ALWAYS WERE
GOOD AT DODGEBALL.

28:04.253 --> 28:05.715
YEAH.

28:08.357 --> 28:10.359
GOT MY VESSEL?

28:10.820 --> 28:13.222
GOT MY MONEY?

28:16.025 --> 28:19.799
PLACE THE VESSEL
ON THE MAT.

28:19.799 --> 28:23.472
UH, IT LOOKS LIKE
IT MIGHT BE TOO BIG.

28:25.704 --> 28:27.236
[AIR HISSES]

28:28.337 --> 28:30.940
RIGHT. YEAH.

28:33.813 --> 28:34.413
HAVE A NICE DAY.

28:34.413 --> 28:37.817
WAIT, WAIT.
THERE'S NOT--I DON'T
HAVE TO SIGN ANYTHING?

28:37.817 --> 28:40.289
I JUST WANT TO MAKE SURE
I GET THE CREDIT.

28:41.150 --> 28:43.422
OK, GREAT.
THANK YOU. PERFECT.

28:43.422 --> 28:46.055
[BUZZER]

28:46.055 --> 28:47.396
WHAT'S THAT?

28:47.396 --> 28:48.327
RED NOTICE.

28:48.327 --> 28:49.258
WELL, WHAT DOES
THAT MEAN?

28:49.258 --> 28:51.460
IT MEANS THERE
WAS SOMETHING OTHER
THAN A SOUL INSIDE.

28:51.460 --> 28:53.432
WHAT'D YOU PUT
IN THERE, POTATOES?

28:53.432 --> 28:55.734
WHAT? NO, NO.
I DIDN'T EVEN--

28:55.734 --> 28:58.367
SAM'S THE ONE
THAT GOT THE SOUL.

28:58.938 --> 28:59.809
[SIGHS]

28:59.809 --> 29:02.311
HEY, DOUCHEBAG.
WHAT DID YOU DO?

29:02.311 --> 29:03.843
I DIDN'T--I DIDN'T
DO ANYTHING.

29:03.843 --> 29:05.114
IT WAS PROBABLY
JUST A GLITCH.

29:05.114 --> 29:06.015
WELL, YOU GOT TO FIX IT.

29:06.015 --> 29:09.248
I--WHAT DO YOU--
I'M NOT FIXING--OW!

29:09.248 --> 29:11.320
NO, NO, NO.
STOP IT.

29:11.320 --> 29:12.321
NO.

29:12.321 --> 29:14.483
[BOTH SHOUTING]

29:14.483 --> 29:16.155
AHH!

29:16.155 --> 29:17.286
OW! OW, OW! OW!

29:17.286 --> 29:21.430
DON'T YOU EVER TRY
TO SCREW ME AGAIN.

29:21.430 --> 29:23.292
AAH.

29:23.292 --> 29:25.995
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

29:31.270 --> 29:32.902
THIS WAS AMAZING.

29:32.902 --> 29:34.473
THANK YOU.

29:34.473 --> 29:36.205
MY PLEASURE.

29:36.205 --> 29:38.948
SO...YOU READY?

29:38.948 --> 29:40.109
COMPLETELY READY.

29:40.109 --> 29:41.350
LET'S DO THIS.

29:41.350 --> 29:44.153
OK.

29:46.816 --> 29:48.257
[SIGHS]

29:48.257 --> 29:52.121
THIS IS THE PERFECT NIGHT
FOR FLYING.

29:52.121 --> 29:53.893
I SAY WE FLY OUT
TO THE WATER,

29:53.893 --> 29:55.494
CRUISE ALONG THE COAST
A LITTLE BIT,

29:55.494 --> 29:57.796
AND THEN
WE'LL FLY INLAND.

30:01.100 --> 30:03.933
I CAN'T DO THIS.

30:03.933 --> 30:04.273
WHAT?

30:04.273 --> 30:06.535
LOOK, I KNOW HOW IMPORTANT
IT IS TO YOU,

30:06.535 --> 30:07.406
BUT I CAN'T DO IT.

30:07.406 --> 30:08.507
I JUST NOW REALIZED
THAT IT'S NOT

30:08.507 --> 30:09.508
THAT I DON'T
LOVE MYSELF ENOUGH,

30:09.508 --> 30:12.581
IT'S THAT I'M SUPER AFRAID
OF FLYING.

30:12.581 --> 30:13.482
AND FALLING.

30:13.482 --> 30:16.445
I'M SORRY, NINA,
I'M SORRY,

30:16.445 --> 30:18.848
BUT NO, NO, NO.

30:18.848 --> 30:22.421
BABY, CAN I TELL YOU
A SECRET?

30:22.421 --> 30:24.093
OF COURSE.

30:24.093 --> 30:24.423
OK.

30:24.423 --> 30:28.197
A LONG TIME AGO
I HAD HEMOPHOBIA.

30:28.197 --> 30:31.260
THAT AIN'T RIGHT.
MY COUSIN'S GAY.

30:31.260 --> 30:35.164
NO. [CHUCKLES]
NO, HEMOPHOBIA.

30:35.164 --> 30:37.166
IT'S A FEAR OF BLOOD.

30:37.166 --> 30:38.407
WELL, YOU LOVE BLOOD.

30:38.407 --> 30:41.440
I KNOW. SEE, THAT'S
WHAT'S CRAZY.

30:41.440 --> 30:44.273
I--I JUST HAD TO
CONFRONT MY FEAR

30:44.273 --> 30:45.945
AND IMMERSE MYSELF
IN IT.

30:45.945 --> 30:47.376
AND THEN ONCE
I DID THAT,

30:47.376 --> 30:49.048
IT WAS GREAT,
I LOVED IT.

30:49.048 --> 30:51.420
AND NOW I COULD
BATHE IN IT
EVERY SINGLE DAY.

30:51.420 --> 30:55.024
THAT'S...NICE FOR YOU.

30:55.024 --> 30:58.157
NO, BUT I CAN
HELP YOU, TOO.

30:58.157 --> 31:02.461
THE QUESTION IS,
WILL YOU LET ME?

31:04.433 --> 31:07.396
YES, NINA,
PLEASE HELP ME.

31:07.396 --> 31:10.139
PERFECT.

31:10.599 --> 31:12.241
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
NO. NO!

31:12.241 --> 31:15.344
[SCREAMING]

31:33.322 --> 31:35.424
AHH!

31:38.197 --> 31:40.369
OW!

31:47.106 --> 31:51.240
YOU JAMMED UP
THE SYSTEM, SAMMY.

31:51.240 --> 31:52.341
OW! OW.

31:52.341 --> 31:53.612
THE SYSTEM IS MADE
OF COGS,

31:53.612 --> 31:56.345
AND EVERY COG
MUST PLAY ITS PART.

31:56.345 --> 31:58.117
OK. PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE.

31:58.117 --> 31:59.548
PLEASE STOP. PLEASE.
PLEASE STOP.

31:59.548 --> 32:04.353
THIS LITTLE COG HERE
HAD TO MUCK UP
THE MACHINERY, HUH?

32:04.353 --> 32:07.356
AND NOW LOOK WHAT
YOU'RE MAKING ME DO.

32:07.356 --> 32:08.327
OH!

32:08.327 --> 32:09.298
AHH.

32:09.298 --> 32:11.130
I'M SORRY.
I'LL GET BILLY.

32:11.130 --> 32:13.232
PLEASE, I'LL GET HIM,
I SWEAR.

32:13.232 --> 32:15.434
NO, YOU WON'T.
YOU CAN'T.

32:15.434 --> 32:20.469
AND THE SAD THING
IS, I WON'T BE ABLE
TO GET HIM EITHER.

32:20.469 --> 32:22.641
THE ENDER WILL.

32:22.641 --> 32:24.943
WHAT IS "THE ENDER"?

32:24.943 --> 32:26.375
MY FAILSAFE.

32:26.375 --> 32:30.379
I HAD IT CREATED
FOR THE RARE OCCASION

32:30.379 --> 32:32.081
WHEN A SOUL GETS LOST

32:32.081 --> 32:35.284
OR SOME IDIOT TRIES
TO BRING A CORPSE BACK
IN ITS PLACE.

32:35.284 --> 32:41.590
THE ENDER IS RELEASED,
TRACKS THE SOUL DOWN,
AND DESTROYS IT.

32:41.590 --> 32:43.332
UTTERLY DESTROYS IT.

32:43.332 --> 32:47.696
AND THAT MEANS ONE LESS
SOUL FOR ME IN HELL.

32:47.696 --> 32:50.699
WELL, JUST CALL
THE ENDER OFF.

32:50.699 --> 32:52.571
OH, GOD!

32:52.571 --> 32:53.702
CALL IT OFF?

32:53.702 --> 32:56.045
CAN YOU CALL OFF
THE TERMINATOR?

32:56.045 --> 32:58.107
YOU CAN'T REASON
WITH IT.

32:58.107 --> 33:00.379
YOU CAN'T STOP IT.

33:00.379 --> 33:02.181
WELL, ISN'T THERE
ANYTHING WE CAN DO?

33:02.181 --> 33:04.413
OH, THE DYE'S
BEEN CAST, BUDDY.

33:04.413 --> 33:05.114
NICE GOING.

33:05.114 --> 33:07.356
YOUR PAL BILLY'S
GONNA WISH HE WAS
BACK IN HELL

33:07.356 --> 33:10.019
BY THE TIME
THE ENDER'S THROUGH
WITH HIM.

33:10.019 --> 33:12.321
[CHUCKLES]

33:21.300 --> 33:22.301
MISSED ME!

33:22.301 --> 33:24.433
OHH!

33:38.417 --> 33:39.448
HEY.
HEY.

33:39.448 --> 33:40.389
THERE'S MY HERO.

33:40.389 --> 33:41.320
I CAME TO WARN YOU.

33:41.320 --> 33:42.451
THERE'S THIS THING
CALLED THE ENDER.

33:42.451 --> 33:45.454
THE DEVIL SAYS IT'S COMING
TO DESTROY YOUR SOUL.

33:45.454 --> 33:46.595
OH, MAN.

33:46.595 --> 33:49.658
WHY CAN'T ANYTHING
EVER GO RIGHT FOR ME?

33:49.658 --> 33:50.299
I'M SORRY, BILLY,

33:50.299 --> 33:54.203
BUT, YOU KNOW,
YOU LOST YOUR VIRGINITY,
AND YOU FELL IN LOVE.

33:54.203 --> 33:57.136
BUT I'M STILL A VIRGIN.

33:57.136 --> 33:57.536
WHAT?

33:57.536 --> 33:59.208
I WANTED TO CONNECT
EMOTIONALLY

33:59.208 --> 34:02.141
BEFORE WE CONNECTED
PHYSICALLY.

34:02.141 --> 34:04.313
[THUNDER]

34:05.274 --> 34:06.445
WELL, YOU BETTER START
CONNECTING PHYSICALLY QUICK

34:06.445 --> 34:09.348
BECAUSE I HAVE A FEELING
YOU'RE RUNNING OUT OF TIME.

34:09.348 --> 34:11.180
I CAN'T RUSH IT, DUDE.

34:11.180 --> 34:12.421
IT'S NOT JUST ABOUT ME,

34:12.421 --> 34:14.283
IT'S ABOUT
CINDY'S PLEASURE, TOO.

34:14.283 --> 34:17.156
IT SAYS SO RIGHT ON
THE CONDOM BOX.

34:17.156 --> 34:18.787
[THUNDER]

34:18.787 --> 34:20.429
MAYBE I CAN BUY YOU
SOME TIME.

34:20.429 --> 34:24.133
BUT WE NEED TO GET
YOU TWO OUT OF HERE.

34:24.133 --> 34:25.194
[THUNDER]

34:25.194 --> 34:25.534
IT WAS AMAZING.

34:25.534 --> 34:28.097
I MEAN, ONE SECOND
I'M ABOUT TO EAT
THE SIDEWALK,

34:28.097 --> 34:30.399
THE NEXT I'M SOARING
THROUGH THE CITY,

34:30.399 --> 34:31.600
CRADLED IN NINA'S ARMS,

34:31.600 --> 34:32.671
HER DEMON BREATH
KEEPING ME WARM.

34:32.671 --> 34:35.804
FOCUS NOW, BENJI.
COME ON, THIS HAS TO BE
THE PERFECT LOVE CHAMBER.

34:35.804 --> 34:36.405
OK, OK.

34:36.405 --> 34:38.377
KID'S GONNA NEED ALL
THE HELP HE CAN GET,
KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

34:38.377 --> 34:39.548
YEAH.
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

34:39.548 --> 34:40.679
JUST ONE SECOND.

34:40.679 --> 34:41.480
[TURNS RADIO ON]

34:41.480 --> 34:43.512
[MORE THAN WORDS
BY EXTREME PLAYING]

34:43.512 --> 34:47.386
NICE.

34:47.386 --> 34:48.487
SMILE, SMILE.

34:48.487 --> 34:52.291
HELLO. WELCOME TO
STORM COMMAND CENTRAL.

34:52.291 --> 34:54.463
WE HAVE
EVERYTHING FOR YOU
TO FEEL SAFE.

34:54.463 --> 34:56.265
WE HAVE FLASHLIGHTS
ON THE DRESSER,

34:56.265 --> 34:58.427
AND THEN WE HAVE
DAIQUIRIS AND LOTION
ON THE NIGHTSTAND.

34:58.427 --> 35:02.331
ALSO, PLEASE FEEL FREE
TO PERUSE MY COLLECTION
OF ADULT EROTICA,

35:02.331 --> 35:04.473
BOTH IN PRINT AND DVD.

35:04.473 --> 35:05.334
UM, WHY DID WE
HAVE TO COME HERE?

35:05.334 --> 35:08.237
WELL, IT'S SAFER TO
WAIT OUT A STORM
WITH FRIENDS.

35:08.237 --> 35:10.239
EXACTLY, SO WE'RE GONNA
LEAVE YOU TWO ALONE

35:10.239 --> 35:11.340
AND CHECK OUT
THE WEATHER CHANNEL.

35:11.340 --> 35:12.411
BILLY,
YOU LET ME KNOW WHEN--

35:12.411 --> 35:14.543
I'LL LET YOU KNOW
WHEN THE STORM PASSES.

35:14.543 --> 35:15.714
GOOD, GREAT.
OK.

35:15.714 --> 35:17.416
LET'S GO.

35:17.416 --> 35:19.248
[CHUCKLES]

35:19.248 --> 35:22.351
COME ON, GUYS.

35:22.351 --> 35:24.893
[THUNDER]

35:25.454 --> 35:27.556
YOU KNOW, I CAN'T BELIEVE
HE'S NOT DONE YET.

35:27.556 --> 35:30.629
I'M IMPRESSED, MAN.
BILLY'S A STALLION.

35:30.629 --> 35:32.831
SMART. GIRLS TALK
TO EACH OTHER.

35:32.831 --> 35:34.603
YOU'RE ONLY AS GOOD
AS YOUR LAST JOB,

35:34.603 --> 35:36.535
YOU KNOW WHAT
I MEAN.

35:39.808 --> 35:42.711
[THUNDER]

35:45.444 --> 35:48.317
OHH!
LOOK!

35:52.651 --> 35:55.824
HOLY CRAP,
THIS IS BAD.

36:04.863 --> 36:07.636
OH, COME ON.
GO, GO, GO, GO.

36:13.272 --> 36:14.373
WE HAVE TO GET
BILLY.

36:14.373 --> 36:16.205
GO, GO.

36:18.407 --> 36:19.778
BILLY, BILLY!
BILLY!

36:19.778 --> 36:21.680
Sam: COME ON, BILLY.

36:21.680 --> 36:23.312
AAH.

36:23.812 --> 36:25.814
AAH!

36:44.773 --> 36:46.535
IS IT GONE?

36:46.535 --> 36:47.636
YEAH.

36:47.636 --> 36:51.380
WHAT JUST HAPPENED?

36:58.787 --> 37:00.289
HEY, GUYS.

37:00.289 --> 37:00.619
HEY.
HEY.

37:00.619 --> 37:02.591
FINALLY UP? YOU DOG.
BOPPIDY BOPPIDY.

37:02.591 --> 37:05.294
HOW DOES IT FEEL TO FINALLY
LOSE YOUR VIRGINITY?

37:05.294 --> 37:06.355
HOW DOES IT FEEL,
BOYS?

37:06.355 --> 37:07.996
LET ME JUST
SHOW YOU.

37:07.996 --> 37:09.828
[GROANS]

37:09.828 --> 37:11.430
OHH.

37:11.430 --> 37:12.401
I WON'T BE
NEEDING THIS.

37:12.401 --> 37:15.334
INTERCOURSE CURED
YOUR ASTHMA?

37:15.334 --> 37:17.636
NO, BUT CINDY'S A
PHARMACEUTICAL REP,

37:17.636 --> 37:19.468
SO SHE GETS THEM
FOR FREE.

37:19.468 --> 37:20.739
OH.
OH.
OH.

37:20.739 --> 37:22.911
CONGRATULATIONS, BUDDY.
ACES.

37:22.911 --> 37:24.012
DO WE KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED,

37:24.012 --> 37:26.315
WHY THE ENDER
DIDN'T COME FOR ME?

37:26.315 --> 37:28.246
BEN HAS A THEORY,
ACTUALLY.

37:28.246 --> 37:30.519
YEAH. SO, DURING
THE ACT OF LOVE,

37:30.519 --> 37:32.481
OR AT THE EXACT MOMENT
OF CONSUMMATION,

37:32.481 --> 37:36.385
2 SOULS BECAME ONE--
YOURS AND CINDY'S.

37:36.385 --> 37:37.856
WELL, IT'S LIKE THE ENDER
LOST YOUR SCENT.

37:37.856 --> 37:41.390
THEY SAY THE DEVIL
HAS NO DOMINION
OVER TRUE LOVE.

37:41.390 --> 37:43.892
SO, UH, AM I OUT?

37:43.892 --> 37:47.396
YEAH, I MEAN, THE DEVIL
THINKS YOU WERE
DESTROYED BY THE ENDER,

37:47.396 --> 37:50.299
AND I DON'T EVEN HAVE
A VESSEL TO CAPTURE YOU,

37:50.299 --> 37:51.740
SO YEAH, THAT'S IT.

37:51.740 --> 37:52.801
HOW COULD I EVER
REPAY YOU GUYS
FOR THIS?

37:52.801 --> 37:57.976
I'M GOING TO SPEND
THE REST OF MY DAYS
MAKING CINDY HAPPY.

37:57.976 --> 37:58.477
Sock: MAN.

37:58.477 --> 38:00.549
GOOD LUCK, BILLY.
GOOD LUCK, BILLY.

38:00.549 --> 38:02.651
BYE.
[SAM SIGHS]

38:02.651 --> 38:05.283
SOMETHING GOOD HAPPENED
HERE TODAY, BOYS.

38:05.283 --> 38:08.857
THE GEEK ESCAPED FROM HELL.
GEEK BANGED A COUGAR.

38:08.857 --> 38:12.290
GEEK WALKS AWAY
A LITTLE LESS OF A GEEK.

38:12.290 --> 38:13.392
AND WE HELPED.

38:13.392 --> 38:15.594
LOOKS LIKE WE'RE HIS
FAIRY BONE-MOTHERS.

38:15.594 --> 38:16.795
THAT IS A NICE FEELING.

38:16.795 --> 38:19.468
FINALLY
A HAPPY ENDING
TO THIS CRAP JOB.

38:19.468 --> 38:20.369
NO KIDDING.

38:20.369 --> 38:22.601
ISN'T THAT MORGAN?
HMM

38:28.537 --> 38:30.679
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

38:31.610 --> 38:32.811
NO!
STOP!

38:32.811 --> 38:34.883
WAIT, MORGAN, STOP!

38:34.883 --> 38:35.884
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

38:35.884 --> 38:36.815
HEY, IT'S THE FELLAS.

38:36.815 --> 38:38.717
OH, DAD TOLD ME
YOU TEND TO FALL

38:38.717 --> 38:39.348
FOR THOSE SOB STORIES,

38:39.348 --> 38:41.450
SO HE SENT ME TO DO THE JOB
YOU COULDN'T DO.

38:41.450 --> 38:42.951
GIVE IT TO ME.
HEY!

38:42.951 --> 38:44.052
EASY, MAN.

38:44.052 --> 38:44.893
YOUR CONSCIENCE IS CLEAR.

38:44.893 --> 38:47.696
YOU DIDN'T WANT TO
SEND HIM TO HELL,
NOW YOU DON'T HAVE TO.

38:47.696 --> 38:50.959
I'LL DO IT.
AND EVERYONE'S HAPPY, RIGHT?

38:50.959 --> 38:52.000
UGH.

38:52.000 --> 38:54.363
[ENGINE REVS]

38:54.363 --> 38:56.365
[TIRES SQUEALING]

38:56.365 --> 38:58.407
[KNOCK ON DOOR,
DOOR OPENS]

38:58.407 --> 39:00.338
HEY, YOU GOT A SECOND?

39:00.338 --> 39:00.869
THAT DEPENDS.

39:00.869 --> 39:04.573
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO PULL
OUT SOME CHAMPAGNE ON ME
AGAIN, ARE YOU?

39:04.573 --> 39:05.444
NO, NO.

39:05.444 --> 39:06.915
UM, THIS IS STRICTLY
WORK-RELATED.

39:06.915 --> 39:09.017
I WANTED TO ASK YOU IF
I COULD LEAVE EARLY TONIGHT.

39:09.017 --> 39:10.479
THERE'S SOMETHING
I HAVE TO DO.

39:10.479 --> 39:13.852
WELL, I'M GOING TO
NEED A BETTER REASON
THAN THAT, SAM.

39:13.852 --> 39:15.053
MORGAN TOOK HIM.

39:15.053 --> 39:17.626
MORGAN TOOK BILLY,
HE'S BACK IN HELL.

39:17.626 --> 39:19.127
OH.

39:19.127 --> 39:20.689
OH, I'M SORRY.

39:20.689 --> 39:21.890
YOU KNOW, IT'S NOT FAIR.

39:21.890 --> 39:23.992
I...I TRY TO DO
SOMETHING GOOD,

39:23.992 --> 39:25.964
SOMETHING TO MAKE
THIS WHOLE THING TOLERABLE,

39:25.964 --> 39:28.497
AND IT'S ALWAYS
TAKEN AWAY FROM ME.

39:28.497 --> 39:30.368
WELL, IF IT MAKES
ANY DIFFERENCE,

39:30.368 --> 39:31.770
YOU HAVE THE REST OF
THE NIGHT OFF

39:31.770 --> 39:33.942
TO DO WHATEVER
YOU NEED TO DO.

39:33.942 --> 39:34.703
THANK YOU.

39:34.703 --> 39:36.745
I'LL MAKE IT UP TO YOU.

39:36.745 --> 39:39.478
OK. YOU WANT COMPANY?

39:39.878 --> 39:42.911
YOU KNOW, AS LONG AS
IT'S NOT A DATE.

39:42.911 --> 39:46.084
NO, IT'S DEFINITELY NOT.

39:48.156 --> 39:49.418
HEY.

39:49.418 --> 39:51.860
WHERE YOU BEEN
HIDING ALL DAY?

39:51.860 --> 39:55.864
AND, UH,
WHERE YOU GOING?

39:55.864 --> 39:58.797
BACK TO JAPAN.

39:58.797 --> 40:00.899
SCHOOL'S OVER,
AND I'M GOING HOME.

40:00.899 --> 40:04.402
GOING HOME? WHY?
YOU WERE IN SCHOOL?

40:04.402 --> 40:06.475
YES, SOCK.
HOTEL MANAGEMENT SCHOOL.

40:06.475 --> 40:08.507
DON'T YOU REMEMBER ME
STUDYING ALL THE TIME?

40:08.507 --> 40:11.810
YOU WERE GONNA LEAVE
AND YOU WEREN'T GONNA
TELL ME, KRISTEN?

40:11.810 --> 40:12.981
HOW COULD YOU DO THAT?

40:12.981 --> 40:15.884
I WAS AFRAID IT WOULD BE
TOO PAINFUL.

40:15.884 --> 40:18.416
OK, WELL, YOU DON'T--YOU
DON'T HAVE TO LEAVE.

40:18.416 --> 40:19.417
I TALKED TO
YOUR DAD ALREADY,

40:19.417 --> 40:20.148
AND ONCE HE GETS TIRED
OF BEATING ME,

40:20.148 --> 40:23.021
WE CAN EVENTUALLY
BE HAPPY TOGETHER,
YOU AND ME.

40:23.021 --> 40:24.152
I'M SO SORRY, SOCK.

40:24.152 --> 40:30.198
IN JAPAN I WAS AFRAID
OF HAVING MY LIFE
PLANNED OUT FOR ME,

40:30.198 --> 40:32.200
SO I DECIDED TO COME
TO AMERICA

40:32.200 --> 40:34.803
TO DISCOVER WHO I WAS.

40:34.803 --> 40:38.136
AND THEN I FOUND YOU.

40:39.007 --> 40:41.009
AND YOU...

40:41.009 --> 40:45.714
HELPED ME DISCOVER
SO MUCH ABOUT MYSELF.

40:47.175 --> 40:50.218
I CAME TO AMERICA AS A GIRL,

40:50.218 --> 40:53.081
BUT BECAUSE OF YOU,

40:53.081 --> 40:55.153
I LEAVE IT AS A WOMAN

40:55.153 --> 40:57.886
WHO HAS DISCOVERED
BOTH HER SEXUALITY

40:57.886 --> 41:02.961
AND HER ABILITY TO MANAGE
AN EXTENDED-STAY HOTEL.

41:02.961 --> 41:04.833
RIGHT.

41:04.833 --> 41:08.767
I OWE ALL OF THAT TO YOU.

41:21.650 --> 41:23.481
UH, KRISTEN.

41:23.481 --> 41:24.252
YES?

41:24.252 --> 41:26.014
[SIGHS]

41:28.687 --> 41:31.189
YOU'RE WELCOME.

41:39.898 --> 41:43.501
Sam: SORRY, BILLY.
DID EVERYTHING WE COULD.

41:43.501 --> 41:46.274
YOU KNOW, THIS GROUND
LOOKS FRESHLY DUG UP.

41:46.274 --> 41:49.277
YEAH, WE DID THAT.

41:49.277 --> 41:51.509
THE--OK.

41:51.509 --> 41:53.511
WELL, HE WAS HAPPY
FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

41:53.511 --> 41:57.015
I MEAN, IT HAS TO
MEAN SOMETHING.

41:57.015 --> 41:58.917
I HOPE SO.

41:58.917 --> 42:01.189
YEAH.

42:02.921 --> 42:03.892
YOU'RE TRESPASSING.

42:03.892 --> 42:05.554
YOU CAN'T BE HERE.

42:05.554 --> 42:07.095
I'M GOING TO CALL
THE COPS.

42:07.095 --> 42:09.527
ALAN?

42:10.629 --> 42:12.561
ALAN!

42:14.162 --> 42:15.263
ALAN!

42:15.263 --> 42:17.205
ALAN!

42:17.205 --> 42:18.937
ALAN!

42:18.937 --> 42:20.969
ALAN, WAIT!

42:22.671 --> 42:25.273
DAMMIT.

42:25.273 --> 42:27.175
ALAN!

42:27.175 --> 42:29.748
I KNOW
YOU'RE OUT THERE.

42:29.748 --> 42:34.252
I'M GONNA FIND YOU!
